article.description: Harvard beats Bryant 86-68 to remain undefeated
article.headline: Harvard beats Bryant 86-68 to remain undefeated
article.linkText: Harvard beats Bryant 86-68 to remain undefeated
article.story: CAMBRIDGE, Mass. -- Wesley Saunders had 25 points and Steve Moundou-Missi scored a career-high 23 as Harvard downed Bryant 86-68 on Wednesday night to extend its home winning streak to 14 games. Saunders shot 7-of-9 from the field while Moundou-Missi was 10-of-15 and led the Crimson (4-0) with nine rebounds. Harvard shot 57.1 percent from the field. Dyami Starks came into the game for Bryant (2-2) as the nation's leading scorer with 100 points through three games, but was held by Harvard to just 11 points. Bryant trailed by 8 with nine minutes to play but Harvard went on a 13-2 run to extend its lead to 76-57. Bryant shot just 2-of-13 from behind the 3-point arc and had 11 shots blocked by the Crimson. Alex Francis led the Bulldogs with 17 points.
